  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Cross-Entropy Method: Pendulum Swing-Up\n\nThe **Cross-Entropy Method (CEM)** is a simple, gradient-free optimization algorithm:\n1. Sample parameter vectors from a Gaussian distribution\n2. Evaluate each by simulating the system\n3. Select the top performers (\"elites\")\n4. Update the distribution mean and std from the elites\n\nNo gradients needed — just simulation + sorting. We use `np_cvode` as the physics engine and `np_randn` for sampling.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "load(\"numerics\")$\nload(\"numerics-sundials\")$\nload(\"numerics-learn\")$\nload(\"ax-plots\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 59,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 1. Pendulum Dynamics\n\nSimple pendulum with torque input $u$:\n$$\\ddot{\\theta} = -\\frac{g}{l}\\sin\\theta - b\\dot{\\theta} + \\frac{u}{ml^2}$$\n\nGoal: swing from **hanging** ($\\theta = \\pi$) to **upright** ($\\theta = 0$).",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Pendulum parameters */\ngv : 9.81$  lp : 1.0$  mp : 1.0$  bp : 0.1$\n\n/* Max torque (saturation) */\nu_max : 5.0$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 60,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 2. Policy and Cost Function\n\nLinear policy in features $[\\sin\\theta, \\cos\\theta, \\omega]$:\n$$u = \\text{clip}(w_1 \\sin\\theta + w_2 \\cos\\theta + w_3 \\omega,\\; -u_{\\max},\\; u_{\\max})$$\n\nThese features are smooth and periodic, unlike raw $\\theta$.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Cost function: simulate one episode, return scalar cost.\n   Lower is better. Penalizes deviation from upright + control effort. */\nsimulate_cost(w1v, w2v, w3v) := block(\n  [u_expr, rhs1, rhs2, tspan_sim, traj, th_col, om_col, cost_state, n_t],\n  /* Build closed-loop dynamics with clipped control */\n  u_expr : max(-u_max, min(u_max,\n    w1v * sin(theta) + w2v * cos(theta) + w3v * omega)),\n  rhs1 : omega,\n  rhs2 : -(gv/lp)*sin(theta) - bp*omega + u_expr/(mp*lp^2),\n  tspan_sim : np_linspace(0, 6, 300),\n  /* Start hanging down: theta = pi */\n  traj : np_cvode([rhs1, rhs2], [t, theta, omega],\n                  [float(%pi), 0.0], tspan_sim, 1e-8, 1e-8),\n  /* Cost: (1 - cos(theta))^2 + 0.1*omega^2, weighted toward final states */\n  th_col : np_slice(traj, all, 1),\n  om_col : np_slice(traj, all, 2),\n  cost_state : np_add(\n    np_pow(np_sub(1.0, np_cos(th_col)), 2),\n    np_scale(0.1, np_pow(om_col, 2))),\n  n_t : first(np_shape(traj)),\n  float(np_mean(cost_state) + 2.0 * np_ref(cost_state, n_t - 1))\n)$\n\n/* Test: cost of zero controller (no torque, hangs at pi forever) */\nprint(\"Zero-controller cost:\", simulate_cost(0.0, 0.0, 0.0))$\n\n/* Wrapper for np_cem: takes an ndarray parameter vector, returns scalar cost */\ncem_cost(w) := simulate_cost(np_ref(w, 0), np_ref(w, 1), np_ref(w, 2))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 61,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Zero-controller cost: 12.0"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 3. Cross-Entropy Method\n\n`np_cem` implements the CEM optimization loop:\n\n1. **Sample**: draw `n_samples` parameter vectors from $\\mathcal{N}(\\mu, \\sigma^2)$\n2. **Evaluate**: run each through the cost function (here, a full ODE simulation)\n3. **Select**: sort by cost, keep the best `n_elites`\n4. **Update**: set $\\mu$ and $\\sigma$ to the elite mean and standard deviation\n\nAfter `n_gens` generations, the distribution has collapsed around a good solution. Failed cost evaluations (e.g., divergent simulations) are automatically assigned $+\\infty$.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "np_seed(42)$\n\n/* Run CEM optimization.\n   cem_cost(w_ndarray) -> scalar is the only user function.\n   np_cem handles sampling, sorting, elite selection, and distribution updates. */\n[best_w, cost_history] : np_cem(cem_cost, 3,\n  n_samples=40, n_elites=8, n_gens=25, sigma0=5.0, sigma_min=0.3)$\n\ncem_mu : np_to_list(best_w)$\nbest_cost_history : np_to_list(cost_history)$\n\nprint(\"Final policy: w =\",\n  map(lambda([x], float(round(x * 100) / 100)), cem_mu))$\nprint(\"Final cost:\", last(best_cost_history))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 62,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
