    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Key Takeaways\n\n- **CEM is simple**: no gradients, no backpropagation — just sample, evaluate, select, repeat\n- **`np_cvode` as the environment**: each CEM sample runs a full ODE simulation as its \"episode\"\n- **Actuator limits matter**: with $u_{\\max} = 5$ the motor cannot reach upright — CEM correctly finds the best achievable policy, parking at the torque-limited equilibrium\n- **Feature engineering matters**: the original $\\cos\\theta$ feature creates a constant bias that shifts the equilibrium away from upright. Replacing it with $1 - \\cos\\theta$ — which vanishes at the target — lets the policy converge to $\\theta = 0$\n- **Maxima's symbolic expressions**: the policy and dynamics are symbolic, compiled to efficient native code by `np_cvode`'s expression mode — no callback overhead\n\nFor higher-dimensional problems, gradient-based methods (using `np_minimize` with `np_compile_gradient`) would be more sample-efficient.",
      "metadata": {}
    }
  ]
}